attributes.background:
We the undersigned:
believe that the Prime Minister has lost the confidence of the country and of Parliament, not least by announcing that he is to resign the office to which he was elected so recently;
believe that his decision to support the USA in its decision to invade Iraq was the worst foreign policy disaster at least since Suez;
believe that representative democracy requires a free and open national election to determine the next Prime Minister rather than having the decision stitched up by the Prime Minister and his party colleagues;
recognising that the Prime Minister's reputation will forever be tarnished by the stain of his actions while in office;
call upon the Prime Minister immediately to resign his office and advise the Queen to dissolve Parliament and call a General Election.
